The book is designed for the use of more advanced student5‚ whether in the Sixth Form of a Public School or at the University. No single speech is better adapted than is the Pro Cluentio to afford a perfect mastery of Ciceronian idiom and vocabulary. Refer- ence has been made throughout to Mr. Roby’s Gram- mars: a feature of the work which should enhance its value in the eyes of those who have a real interest in Syntax.
